From bec448373a4509fb6b8e38f502642008da252c29 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guru Pratap Sharma <guruprat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Jun 2025 21:27:46 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL hostapd: Select Random Channel Change for
 AFC

Enhance the AFC (Automatic Frequency Control) retail feature to support
random channel selection upon receiving the EVENT_AFC_RECEIVED event.

1. Select a random channel when the event is received.
2. Switch to the best power mode for the selected channel.
3. Trigger a Channel Switch Announcement (CSA) on the selected channel.

Ensure that AFC-related transitions are handled predictably and robustly
to improve system reliability under retail AFC conditions.

Feature: AFC
Patch-dependency: n00-001-hostapd-add-support-for-6GHz-operation.patch,
r65-QSDK-HOSTAPD-Implement-Min-PSD-Calculation-and-Punct.patch,
r66-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Fetch-AFC-support-from-wiphy.patch,
r66-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Handle-AFC-Channel-Change.patch,
r72-a-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-6-GHz-power-mode-channels-.patch,
r72-b-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Print-6-GHz-power-mode-cha.patch,
r72-c-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Store-6-GHz-power-mode-cha.patch,
r72-d-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Clean-up-and-refactor-6-GH.patch,
r72-e-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Support-for-SP-and-Punctur.patch,
r72-f-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Add-6-GHz-regulatory-struc.patch,
r72-g-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Add-6-GHz-base-regulatory-.patch,
r72-h-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Apply-best-power-mode-for-.patch,
r72-i-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Fix-6-GHz-power-mode-confi.patch,
r72-j-UPSTREAM-PROTOCOL-hostapd-Handle-empty-AFC-power-eve.patch
Tag: 6G_REGULATORY

Signed-off-by: Guru Pratap Sharma <guruprat@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
